"""v2-S05 Stage E.TPS — expand each subject's K=4 seed constellation
into a per-cell mapping and score against the bench.

Design
------
Stage D (v2-S04) produced a best K=4 (CZ, HCR) anchor constellation per
subject (best aniso-similarity RMSE).  Here we use those four anchors
to define the global transform — replacing the LP+sz-pin warmstart that
v2-S03 used — and fall back on standard NN matching for the cell pairs.

Variants:
- ``E_TPS_aniso``     — fit aniso-similarity (R, scales, t) on K=4
                         anchors, apply to all CZ → NN-match HCR GFP+.
- ``E_TPS_aniso_icp`` — same warmstart, then run M3-style locked-scale
                         rigid ICP (residual SE(3)) on top.

K=4 in 3D constrains a 9-DOF aniso fit with 3 residual DOF; the v2-S04
RMSE on these anchors (≤ 1.7 µm except 767018 ≈ 1.7) confirms the
transform is well-specified.  We do NOT use thin-plate-spline because
K=4 is right at the degeneracy boundary for 3D TPS — keeping the
anchored model affine is more honest.

Inputs
------
- ``v2_S04_seed_constellation/step2_all_subjects_summary_wide.csv``
- ``v2_S04_seed_constellation/step1_{sid}_wide_topslab_candidates.csv``
  (used to look up CZ warped positions; the HCR µm comes from
  ``s.hcr_centroids`` via ``centroid_helpers``).

Outputs
-------
- ``bench_e_tps_results.csv``
- ``bench_e_tps.log``
"""
